align=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> Miriel,<br>
<br>
These can help you somewhat now with Lullabye, as it is Charisma-dependent.  Especially if they will get you over 100 - I've noticed a big difference in resists after I crossed that threshold.  The magic number for us seems to be about 120-125.<br>
<br>
If you can do this and maintain your AC, you're in great shape.  You're still a viable meleer for a while, so you need to keep that AC up.  Also, the monsters will certainly not like you at all after Lullaby wears off, so you become top of their hate list for a little while - need that AC to keep them off of you!<br>
<br>
And remember - there's an 'older' bard happy to make plate for you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Actually, if you don't mind wearing medium, I may have some medium pieces you can have - will save weight on that nasty bronze stuff...<br>
<br>
